HEADWORD: Sulphamide
<hw>Sulph*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a series of amido compounds obtained by treating
sulphuryl chloride with various amines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

